# Git at end of tasks

When you finish implementing or fixing something in this repo:

1. Run `git status` and stage all intended changes (never commit `.env` or secrets).
2. Commit with a clear message (`type(scope): summary`).
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (usually `master`).

If there is nothing to commit, say so briefly.
